PN,42102
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1778350335
OL,3,CVoters choose a different 'change' as
OL,4,CReform UK rout Labour in the North East
OL,6,FWearside has chosen Labour MPs for
OL,7,Fdecades and Sunderland City Council
OL,8,Fhad been under the party's control
OL,9,Fsince its creation in the 1970s.
OL,11,FAs Nigel Farage put it from a victory
OL,12,Frally (in Essex) on Friday night:
OL,13,F"Labour used to weigh the votes." But,
OL,14,Fin Thursday's council election, his
OL,15,Fparty, Reform UK "absolutely walked
OL,16,Fit."
OL,18,FThey won 58 of Sunderland's 75 seats,
OL,19,Freducing Labour to just five.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G2/22
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42103
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1778350335
OL,3,CVoters choose a different 'change' as
OL,4,CReform UK rout Labour in the North East
OL,6,FThat actually came as little surprise
OL,7,F- such is the way Reform are tapping
OL,8,Finto the disdain many voters now feel
OL,9,Ftowards the traditional big two
OL,10,Fparties.
OL,12,FWhen I asked a man in Sunderland city
OL,13,Fcentre on Friday morning why he'd
OL,14,Fvoted for Reform, he replied: "It's
OL,15,Fabout time the Labour government got
OL,16,Fkicked out of the city."
OL,18,FThat nods to how these local results
OL,19,Fwere, more than anything, a reflection
OL,20,Fof the national mood.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G3/22
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42104
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1778350335
OL,3,CVoters choose a different 'change' as
OL,4,CReform UK rout Labour in the North East
OL,6,FAnother chap acknowledged there has
OL,7,F"quite a bit of investment" in
OL,8,FSunderland recently under the Labour
OL,9,Fcouncil's watch - but the cost of the
OL,10,Fliving is "sticking in people's
OL,11,Fthroats."
OL,13,FThat kind of economic-political
OL,14,Fgravity is hard to overcome for any
OL,15,Fincumbents.
OL,17,FAnother voter said Nigel Farage "seems
OL,18,Fcanny". That (with its vague northern
OL,19,Fslang meaning) word might just sum up
OL,20,Fthe appeal of his every-man persona.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G4/22
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
