OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1778350335
OL,3,CVoters choose a different 'change' as
OL,4,CReform UK rout Labour in the North East
OL,6,FA woman told me simply: "I think we
OL,7,Fneed a change."
OL,9,FOf course that's what Labour promised
OL,10,Fto deliver for the country at the
OL,11,Fgeneral election, when they won 26 of
OL,12,Fthe 27 parliamentary seats in the
OL,13,FNorth East.
OL,15,FBut so many people have seen little
OL,16,Fsign of positive change, and plenty of
OL,17,Fu-turns and controversies over the
OL,18,Flast two years instead.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G5/22
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42106
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1778350335
OL,3,CVoters choose a different 'change' as
OL,4,CReform UK rout Labour in the North East
OL,6,FMartin Gannon, the Labour leader of
OL,7,FGateshead Council who had just lost
OL,8,Fhis seat, told us he felt these
OL,9,Felections had seen "substantial
OL,10,Fnumbers of people prepared to vote for
OL,11,Fanything other than the Labour Party."
OL,13,FThe Conservatives were on the
OL,14,Freceiving end of a similar vibe at the
OL,15,Fend of their time in government in
OL,16,F2024.
OL,18,FLabour were the beneficiaries then,
OL,19,Fand Reform are now.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G6/22
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42107
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1778350335
OL,3,CVoters choose a different 'change' as
OL,4,CReform UK rout Labour in the North East
OL,6,FThey also claimed a comfortable
OL,7,Fmajority in Gateshead, where Labour
OL,8,Fhad also run the council for more than
OL,9,F50 years.
OL,11,FWhy did Labour lose those councils
OL,12,Fnow, when they didn't during their
OL,13,Flast period in power at Westminster
OL,14,Funder Blair and Brown?
OL,16,FWell, Starmer and his government
OL,17,Fappear almost unprecedentedly
OL,18,Funpopular, politics has become more
OL,19,Fvolatile, voters are less loyal, and
OL,20,Fthere are now more viable alternatives.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G7/22
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42108
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1778350335
OL,3,CVoters choose a different 'change' as
OL,4,CReform UK rout Labour in the North East
OL,6,FOn my slightly amended Great North Run
OL,7,Froute through the council areas last
OL,8,Fmonth, I spoke to people attracted by
OL,9,FReform as "something different" and to
OL,10,Fthe Green Party because they were
OL,11,F"disappointed" with the Labour
OL,12,Fgovernment.
OL,14,FIt seems the Greens took a substantial
OL,15,Fnumber of votes from Labour from the
OL,16,Fleft this week, often making it easier
OL,17,Ffor Reform to win seats.
OL,19,FThe first past the post system
OL,20,Fexaggerates seat numbers compared to
OL,21,Fvote shares.
OL,26,@qD@KOUqD@_O]sD@AOUsD@NO]
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G8/22
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42109
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1778350335
OL,3,CVoters choose a different 'change' as
OL,4,CReform UK rout Labour in the North East
OL,6,FIn South Tyneside, where Labour were
OL,7,Fin minority control, they were left
OL,8,Fwith just a single councillor, while
OL,9,FReform claimed a big majority on 41.
OL,11,FReform won all 12 seats on offer in
OL,12,FHartlepool. A third of the council was
OL,13,Fup for election this year, it's now
OL,14,Funder no overall control.
OL,16,FIt's a place that sums up how quickly
OL,17,Fpolitics in the North East continues
OL,18,Fto change.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G9/22
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
