PN,42110
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1778350335
OL,3,CVoters choose a different 'change' as
OL,4,CReform UK rout Labour in the North East
OL,6,FJust five years ago, in May 2021,
OL,7,FPrime Minister Boris Johnson's
OL,8,FConservatives won a historic
OL,9,Fparliamentary by-election from Labour
OL,10,Fin Hartlepool, causing Keir Starmer to
OL,11,Fconsider resigning as party leader.
OL,13,FIn the spring of 2024, Labour first
OL,14,Fwon majority control on Hartlepool
OL,15,FBorough Council, then won back the
OL,16,Fparliamentary seat as part of
OL,17,FStarmer's landslide.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}       G10/22
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42111
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1778350335
OL,3,CVoters choose a different 'change' as
OL,4,CReform UK rout Labour in the North East
OL,6,FNow they've lost that council majority
OL,7,Fagain, and Hartlepool's Labour MP is
OL,8,Fone of the leading voices calling on
OL,9,Fthe Prime Minister to quit.
OL,11,FJonathan Brash did so a fortnight ago
OL,12,Famid the scandal around Starmer's
OL,13,Fdecision to appoint Peter Mandelson as
OL,14,FUS ambassador, and did so again in the
OL,15,Fearly hours of Friday morning.
OL,17,FHis wife, Pamela Hargreaves, had been
OL,18,Fleading the council in Hartlepool but
OL,19,Flost her seat.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}       G11/22
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42112
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1778350335
OL,3,CVoters choose a different 'change' as
OL,4,CReform UK rout Labour in the North East
OL,6,FIn fact, all five Labour council
OL,7,Fleaders up for election in the North
OL,8,FEast on Thursday lost their individual
OL,9,Fseats.
OL,11,FThe Conservatives also lost their
OL,12,Ffinal councillors in Hartlepool. They
OL,13,Fdid okay in North Tyneside, where a
OL,14,Fthird of seats were also up for
OL,15,Felection and Labour's majority was
OL,16,Fsecure.
OL,18,FBut in the four councils in the region
OL,19,Fwith all-out elections on Thursday,
OL,20,Fthe Tories did not win a single seat.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}       G12/22
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42113
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1778350335
OL,3,CVoters choose a different 'change' as
OL,4,CReform UK rout Labour in the North East
OL,6,FTyneside and Wearside aren't normally
OL,7,Fareas of Conservative strength, but
OL,8,Flet's not forget that the party had 11
OL,9,FMPs in the North East two years ago,
OL,10,Fbefore that number was cut to one at
OL,11,Fthe general election.
OL,13,FLocal elections can often be an
OL,14,Fopportunity to register protest and
OL,15,Fthe next time voters are asked to
OL,16,Fchoose a Prime Minister and a
OL,17,Fgovernment might well see more people
OL,18,Freturn to the more established
OL,19,Fparties, but that's far from
OL,20,Fguaranteed.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}       G13/22
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42114
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1778350335
OL,3,CVoters choose a different 'change' as
OL,4,CReform UK rout Labour in the North East
OL,6,FOur region is not generally a happy
OL,7,Fhunting ground for the third party of
OL,8,Fthe recent decades, the Liberal
OL,9,FDemocrats, but they held up pretty
OL,10,Fwell this week, as the main opposition
OL,11,F- now to Reform - in Sunderland and
OL,12,FGateshead.
OL,14,FThey came out as the largest party in
OL,15,FNewcastle, just ahead of the Greens
OL,16,Fand Reform.
OL,18,FAnother council lost by Labour, and
OL,19,Four clearest example of this new era
OL,20,Fof multi-party politics at work.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}       G14/22
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42115
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1778350335
OL,3,CVoters choose a different 'change' as
OL,4,CReform UK rout Labour in the North East
OL,6,FA coalition between the Lib Dems and
OL,7,Fthe Green Party is now likely, though
OL,8,Fthe Greens may need to expel several
OL,9,Fcouncillors accused of antisemitic
OL,10,Fremarks.
OL,12,FSimilarly, Reform UK have several new
OL,13,FSunderland councillors accused of
OL,14,Fmaking racist comments on social media.
OL,16,FWith these victories of course comes
OL,17,Fmore scrutiny and more potential for
OL,18,Fproblems that could knock Nigel Farage
OL,19,Foff the path to Downing Street.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}       G15/22
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42116
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1778350335
OL,3,CVoters choose a different 'change' as
OL,4,CReform UK rout Labour in the North East
OL,6,FKeir Starmer is clinging on in there
OL,7,Ffor now.
OL,9,FAmong the growing number of Labour
OL,10,Fpoliticians calling for him to quit
OL,11,Fare Middlesbrough and Thornaby East MP
OL,12,FAndy McDonald, who said: "We need a
OL,13,Fchange of leader tied to change of
OL,14,Fpolicy - for a radical economic
OL,15,Fvision, with better incomes and higher
OL,16,Fliving standards."
OL,18,FBlyth and Ashington MP Ian Lavery
OL,19,Fwarned that Starmer "could end the
OL,20,FLabour Party forever".
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}       G16/22
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42117
SC,0017
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1778350335
OL,3,CVoters choose a different 'change' as
OL,4,CReform UK rout Labour in the North East
OL,6,FThey are familiar critics from the
OL,7,Fleft of the party, and crucially his
OL,8,Fcabinet have not (publicly) moved
OL,9,Fagainst him yet.
OL,11,FThe Education Secretary and Houghton
OL,12,Fand Sunderland South MP Bridget
OL,13,FPhillipson was one of those offering
OL,14,Fsupport. She wrote: "Keir has won
OL,15,Fbefore, he can win again. We need to
OL,16,Fdeliver change, not chaos."
OL,18,FThe Prime Minister has insisted he is
OL,19,F"not going to walk away", and is due
OL,20,Fto give a big speech on Monday aiming
OL,21,Fto shore up his position.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}       G17/22
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42118
SC,0018
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1778350335
OL,3,CVoters choose a different 'change' as
OL,4,CReform UK rout Labour in the North East
OL,6,FOne of his key themes, designed in
OL,7,Fpart to appeal to Europhiles who may
OL,8,Fhave gone with the Greens or Lib Dems,
OL,9,Fwill be closer cooperation with the EU.
OL,11,FSo to return to where I started - of
OL,12,Fcourse there was another time in not-
OL,13,Fso-distant memory when the whole
OL,14,Fcountry (or at least political
OL,15,Fobsessives like me) watched Sunderland
OL,16,Fto see exactly which way the votes
OL,17,Fwould stack up.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}       G18/22
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42119
SC,0019
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1778350335
OL,3,CVoters choose a different 'change' as
OL,4,CReform UK rout Labour in the North East
OL,6,FThat same venue at Silksworth leisure
OL,7,Fcentre was where the city famously
OL,8,Fbecame the first to declare for Brexit
OL,9,Fin June 2016.
OL,11,FThat vote played a key role in
OL,12,Fsevering old party loyalties,
OL,13,Fparticular for Labour in places like
OL,14,Fthe North East.
OL,16,FAnd voters are still largely divided
OL,17,Falong Leave / Remain lines now - as
OL,18,Fexplained by ITV News' election
OL,19,Fanalyst Professor Jane Green recently.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}       G19/22
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42120
SC,0020
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1778350335
OL,3,CVoters choose a different 'change' as
OL,4,CReform UK rout Labour in the North East
OL,6,FNow, finally, nearly a decade on from
OL,7,Fthat EU referendum vote, Nigel
OL,8,FFarage's latest party will run
OL,9,FSunderland and two neighbouring
OL,10,Fcouncils.
OL,12,FIt's actually three, after they won
OL,13,Fcontrol of Durham County Council in
OL,14,Fsimilar fashion last May.
OL,16,FThey haven't acted too dramatically
OL,17,Fyet there, pointing proudly to
OL,18,Flimiting this year's council tax rise
OL,19,Fto 2% - though that's meant removing
OL,20,Fdiscounts from some lower-income
OL,21,Fresidents.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}       G20/22
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
